injuries.comment: Waiters had surgery in his left ankle in January, and the team is unsure if he will be ready for training camp, according to Ira Winderman of the South Florida Sun-Sentinel.
The Wizards announced that Porter had a procedure done to address the buildup of blood flow in the area of a contusion of his leg. He's out indefinitely.
Heyward had a ankle procedure where the screws were removed from his broken fibula. He's expected to resume basketball activities in 6-8 weeks, according to Gary Washburn of The Boston Globe.

The Celtics announced that Irving underwent a procedure on Saturday (Apr. 7) to remove a couple of screws from his left patella from an injury he suffered in 2015. He's expected to take 4-5 months to recover.
Theis said he's participating in drills and is expecting to be 100 percent healthy by the time training camp rolls around, according to Gary Washburn of the Boston Globe.
Smith is dealing with a Jones fracture in his foot that he suffered during a summer developmental camp, according to Ian Begley of ESPN. There is no timetable for his return.
The 76ers announced that Covington had surgery to repair the extensor tendon in his left middle finger. He will be re-evaluated in a few weeks.
The Knicks announced Porzingis had successful surgery Tuesday (Feb 13) to repair a torn ACL in his left knee.
Hollis-Jefferson is dealing with a left abductor strain and is expected to start rehab soon, according to Brian Lewis of the New York Post.
Henson is listed as out for Game Seven on Saturday (Apr. 28) against the Celtics, according to head coach Joe Prunty.
Leuer had off-season knee surgery. The team announced they will update his condition before the start of training camp, according to Ansar Khan of MLive.com.
The Bulls announced G Denzel Valentine will undergo surgery on his left knee and he'll miss the rest of the season.
Ball will undergo arthroscopic surgery on his left knee, but he's expected to be ready for the start of the regular season, according to Sam Amick of NBA Insider.
The Kings announced Giles is on track with his rehabilitation but they would prefer to have him focus on his individual rehab with a goal of being ready for the 2018 Las Vegas Summer League.
The Kings announced that Bogdanovic had surgery on his left knee. He's expected to resume full basketball activities in 8-10 weeks.
Jackson is expected to be ready to play in the Summer League with the team, according to Will Guillory of the New Orleans Times-Picayune.
The Pelicans announced Ajinca will be out for four-to-six months following successful surgery on his left patellar tendon.

Carter had surgery on his right thumb after suffering a ligament rupture, according to Michael Wallace of the team's official website. There team hopes to know soon what a timetable for recovery looks like.

Sefolosha is making progress, but is still at least another month or so away from returning to normal summer training, according to Ben Dowsett of The Athletic. The expectation is that he's healthy and ready for the start of the 2018-2019 season.
Roberson had arthroscopic surgery on his left knee, according to Royce Young of ESPN.
George had surgery on his knee and is expected to return to basketball activities in 6-8 weeks, according to Marc J. Spears of TheUndefeated.com.
Jon Krawczynski of The Athletic Minnesota reports, Timberwolves coach Tom Thibodeau said Patton will miss most of the fall recovering from foot surgery.
Porter underwent his second back surgery  according to Steve Aschburner of NBA.com
Plumlee had surgery to repair a core muscle, according to Harrison Wind of BSNDenver.com. The expectation is that he will be ready by training camp.
